10 Years Later: Remembering Jason Collier 
Jason Collier was a standout on the Springfield Catholic Central High School boys basketball team, winning a state title in 1996. He later landed at Indiana and Georgia Tech, before making his mark in the NBA. The 7-foot Collier was a first round draft pick and played five years in the NBA for the Milwaukee Bucks and Atlanta Hawks. He died at age 28 from a heart issue on Oct. 15, 2005. 
PHOTOS: President Obama visits Roseburg and Seattle 
Obama is meeting with families of the victims of the Oct. 1, shooting at Umpqua Community College, as part of a four-day West Coast tour. Obama is also scheduled to attend a fundraiser event afterward in Seattle with Sen. Patty Murray.
